<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════ 01 AI INSIGHTS ═══════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="section">
  <div class="section-title">01 — AI Insights</div>
  <div class="insights-box">
    <p>
      TDM's outreach engine is <strong>fully live and producing early-stage engagement</strong> across both LinkedIn (Prosp) and email (MMai). Across 8 LinkedIn campaigns, <strong>1,269 connection requests</strong> were sent resulting in <strong>174 accepted invites (13.7%)</strong>, <strong>146 conversations started</strong>, and <strong>33 replies</strong>. Simultaneously, <strong>3,913 email executions</strong> across 18 sequences are generating a <strong>3.53% open rate</strong> and <strong>3.68% click rate</strong> — healthy baseline numbers for a cold outreach program.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>The standout performer is Chris Torbit's ProfServices IT LinkedIn campaign</strong> — 236 requests sent, 75 accepted (31.8%), 61 conversations started, and 20 replies. That acceptance rate is more than double the portfolio average and the conversation volume is nearly 3x any other campaign. The audience-message fit here is clearly working and this campaign is the model to replicate.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Diana's Manufacturing IT AI campaign has the highest reply quality</strong> — 5 replies from just 19 accepted contacts is a 38.5% reply-to-accepted rate, meaning once someone connects, they're highly likely to engage. Volume is the only constraint here. In contrast, Diana's Manufacturing IT Demand Gen campaign is the weakest in the portfolio with a 3.6% acceptance rate and zero replies — the audience targeting or connection message needs a reset.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>The primary gap across both channels is the conversion from conversation to meeting.</strong> 33 LinkedIn replies and 0 email replies have not produced any booked meetings. This is expected at program inception but is the immediate optimization priority. Booking links, softer CTAs, and reply-ask language in follow-up steps will be the focus for the next period.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

